21/12/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The district court in Belgrade announced on Friday (December 19th) that Bosnian Serb war crimes suspect Nenad Malic has been remanded for 30 days. 
Malic is suspected of murdering two Muslim civilians and wounding a third on December 21st, 1992 at the Fontana motel in Stari Majdan, Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
(B92, Kurir, RTS - 19/12/08)
